# Images live in Cloudflare R2, never in git.
#
# The archive is ~14,000 deck photos (~3GB of thumb+medium, plus originals). Git
# cannot absorb that: the repo would balloon and every CI clone would drag it
# along. The site loads them from the bucket via NEXT_PUBLIC_MEDIA_BASE_URL
# (.env.production); `npm run upload:r2` pushes new derivatives to the bucket.
# Originals stay on the ingest machine as the cold archive.
public/media/

# local worker log
accumulate.log

# The snapshot is a build artifact: regenerated from Neon daily, ~3MB of new git
# objects per commit, and it grows with the archive. It lives in R2 instead and
# the build fetches it (scripts/fetch-snapshot.mjs). Only snapshot.meta.json —
# a few hundred bytes — is committed, to trigger the Vercel redeploy.
src/generated/data.json
